WEBVTT

00:02.210 --> 00:03.253
{\an7}Ned: IN A MIDDLE SCHOOL
FULL OF BULLIES,

00:03.336 --> 00:04.254
{\an7}Ned: IN A MIDDLE SCHOOL
FULL OF BULLIES,

00:04.337 --> 00:05.630
{\an8}INSANE TEACHERS,

00:05.714 --> 00:08.258
{\an8}AND GROSS SCHOOL LUNCHES,

00:08.341 --> 00:09.342
{\an8}NED BIGBY--THAT'S ME--

00:09.426 --> 00:12.303
{\an7}AND MY TWO BEST FRIENDS
TRY TO DO THE IMPOSSIBLE:

00:12.387 --> 00:14.597
{\an8}CREATE A GUIDE THAT
WILL HELP YOU SURVIVE SCHOOL.

00:14.681 --> 00:16.766
{\an8}Man: ♪ TURN IT UP ♪

00:16.850 --> 00:18.977
{\an8}♪ LOOKING OUT ♪

00:19.060 --> 00:21.688
{\an8}♪ I'LL SURVIVE
WITH NO DOUBT ♪

00:21.771 --> 00:23.523
{\an8}♪ NEVER FEAR ♪

00:23.606 --> 00:25.024
{\an8}♪ BRING IT ON ♪

00:25.108 --> 00:27.569
{\an7}♪ BREAKING DOWN
WHAT'S IN MY WAY ♪

00:27.652 --> 00:32.198
{\an8}♪ AND I'M ♪

00:32.281 --> 00:35.118
{\an7}♪ FINDING MY PLACE
IN THIS WORLD ♪

00:35.201 --> 00:36.953
{\an8}♪ AND I'M... ♪

00:37.036 --> 00:39.330
{\an8}Ned: "NED'S DECLASSIFIED
SCHOOL SURVIVAL GUIDE."

00:39.414 --> 00:40.540
{\an8}YOUR RESULTS MAY VARY.

00:40.623 --> 00:44.043
{\an8}CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION

00:44.127 --> 00:47.130
{\an8}AND NICKELODEON

00:47.213 --> 00:48.131
[PING]

00:59.434 --> 01:02.228
♪ YEAH-AH ♪

01:02.312 --> 01:05.272
♪ OH-OH ♪

01:09.569 --> 01:12.238
AAAH!

01:12.322 --> 01:15.950
{\an5}Ned: WHEN THERE'S TROUBLE,
MISCHIEF, OR VANDALISM
AT SCHOOL,

01:16.034 --> 01:18.745
{\an1}ONE PERSON IS CALLED
TO CRACK THE CRIME

01:18.828 --> 01:20.663
AND PUNISH THOSE RESPONSIBLE--

01:20.747 --> 01:24.042
THE ASSISTANT PRINCIPAL,
OR AS HE'S KNOWN AT POLK,

01:24.125 --> 01:28.379
VICE PRINCIPAL CRUBBS.

01:28.463 --> 01:30.673
THAT SANDER WAS
A PIECE OF CRUD,

01:30.757 --> 01:32.509
BUT IT WAS STILL
PART OF THE SHOP.

01:32.592 --> 01:35.553
RELAX. I'LL PUT IN
AN EMERGENCY REQUISITION

01:35.637 --> 01:37.138
FOR A NEW SANDER.

01:37.222 --> 01:39.098
PAGE 27.
I CIRCLED IT.

01:39.182 --> 01:40.183
THAT'S A LOVELY SELECTION.

01:40.266 --> 01:47.023
NOW, I'LL ANALYZE THESE
SAMPLES ON MY COMPUTER

01:47.106 --> 01:50.819
{\an1}AND CATCH THE CRETIN
WHO SMASHED YOUR SANDER.

01:53.279 --> 01:56.533
IT FROZE?
I HATE THIS COMPUTER.

01:57.951 --> 02:00.411
HUH?

02:00.495 --> 02:02.247
HELLO!

02:06.334 --> 02:10.213
CHEEDLE: THE MESSY ORANGEY
RESIDUE FROM CHEESE PUFFS.

02:10.295 --> 02:14.217
SO WE FIND THE PUFFS, WE
FIND THE SANDER SMASHER.

02:16.135 --> 02:19.347
[TOGETHER]
HEY. WHAT'S GOING ON?

02:19.430 --> 02:20.306
BUSTED.

02:33.945 --> 02:34.988
BUT WE'RE NOT
THE SANDER SMASHERS.

02:35.071 --> 02:39.242
OUR ONLY CRIME IS
LOVING CHEESE PUFFS.

02:39.325 --> 02:42.120
{\an1}WELL, WE'LL SEE WHAT
MY COMPUTER THINKS

02:42.203 --> 02:44.247
{\an1}WHEN IT CONNECTS YOU
TO THE CRIME.

02:44.330 --> 02:47.792
{\an1}AND THEN YOU'LL DO
SOME TIME.

02:47.876 --> 02:50.712
THIS COMPUTER STINKS!

02:50.795 --> 02:54.340
{\an1}HOW CAN I SAZZA FRAZZA
BAGGA FRAGGA...

02:54.424 --> 02:57.302
[GARBLED CURSING]

02:59.637 --> 03:00.930
[FEEDBACK]

03:03.266 --> 03:05.393
DISREGARD
THAT LAST THING I SAID.

03:05.476 --> 03:10.106
SO WHAT WERE YOU DOING
OUT OF CLASS

03:10.189 --> 03:14.611
WITH A BAG OF CHEESE PUFFS?

03:14.694 --> 03:15.778
{\an1}ONE VICE PRINCIPAL TIP
THAT ALWAYS WORKS FOR ME

03:15.862 --> 03:18.823
{\an8}IS ALWAYS TELL THE TRUTH.

03:18.907 --> 03:20.283
{\an7}THEY LOVE THE HONESTY
AND THEY'LL SHOW IT

03:20.366 --> 03:24.287
BY MAKING YOUR PUNISHMENT
LIGHTER.

03:24.370 --> 03:28.249
WE WERE...

03:28.333 --> 03:31.586
[MUFFLED]

03:35.548 --> 03:39.093
OK. YOU'RE OFF THE HOOK
FOR THE SANDER.

03:39.177 --> 03:41.054
{\an1}BUT YOU'RE CLAPPING ERASERS
LATER FOR HALL PASS ABUSE

03:41.137 --> 03:44.098
AND ILLEGAL BATHROOM
DECORATION.

03:44.182 --> 03:48.603
SO THAT ONLY
LEAVES ONE SUSPECT.

03:48.686 --> 03:49.604
[SIREN]

03:49.687 --> 03:52.565
{\an5}I'M INNOCENT.
I WAS FRAMED.
I DIDN'T DO IT.

03:52.649 --> 03:55.985
WAIT. WHAT DID I
DIDN'T DO?

03:56.069 --> 03:58.154
AND REMEMBER, IF YOU DO LIE
TO A VICE PRINCIPAL

03:58.237 --> 03:59.405
ON A REGULAR BASIS,

03:59.489 --> 04:00.740
{\an7}THEY'LL NEVER BELIEVE YOU
WHEN YOU'RE ACTUALLY

04:00.823 --> 04:02.325
{\an8}TELLING THE TRUTH.

04:04.702 --> 04:06.829
AAH!

04:06.913 --> 04:10.083
WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE YOU'VE
BEEN CAUGHT ORANGE HANDED.

04:10.166 --> 04:13.920
WAIT. WHO DOESN'T
LOVE CHEESE PUFFS?

04:14.003 --> 04:16.798
THEY'RE LIKE A BAG
FULL OF SMILES. SEE?

04:16.880 --> 04:18.216
I'VE HAD IT WITH YOU, LOOMER,

04:18.298 --> 04:20.510
{\an1}AND WHEN MY COMPUTER
CONNECTS YOU TO THE CRIME,

04:20.593 --> 04:22.178
YOU'LL BE EXPELLED.

04:22.262 --> 04:22.929
EXPELLED? EXPELLED!

04:23.012 --> 04:25.515
WAIT. WHAT DOES
EXPELLED MEAN?

04:25.598 --> 04:29.727
{\an1}IT MEANS THIS IS YOUR LAST DAY
IN THIS SCHOOL FOREVER.

04:29.811 --> 04:30.853
BRING!

04:30.937 --> 04:32.772
BUT THIS TIME
I'M NOT LYING.

04:32.855 --> 04:34.065
COME ON.

04:37.694 --> 04:39.237
{\an1}I THINK LOOMER'S
INNOCENT.

04:39.320 --> 04:40.780
{\an1}THOSE WERE TEARS
OF TRUTH.

04:40.863 --> 04:41.948
BUT THIS COULD
GET RID OF

04:42.031 --> 04:43.408
OUR LOOMER
PROBLEM FOREVER.

04:43.491 --> 04:47.286
{\an4}HEY. THE GUIDE WAS
CREATED TO HELP KIDS
SURVIVE SCHOOL.

04:47.370 --> 04:49.706
{\an1}AND IF LOOMER'S INNOCENT,
WE GOT TO HELP HIM.

04:49.789 --> 04:51.666
{\an1}IT'S LIKE THE CODE
OF THE GUIDE.

04:51.749 --> 04:52.041
Ned: YOU'RE RIGHT.

04:52.125 --> 04:54.043
BUT NO WAY!

04:54.127 --> 04:55.962
HA HA.

04:56.045 --> 04:59.382
{\an5}DON'T SHOOT US THAT
"I'M DISAPPOINTED
IN YOU" LOOK.

04:59.465 --> 05:02.593
IT DOESN'T WORK
ON US ANYMORE.

05:02.677 --> 05:05.638
HUH. YEAH.

05:21.154 --> 05:22.905
♪ YEOWWW! ♪

05:22.989 --> 05:26.284
♪ YOU'RE NO GOOD FOR ME ♪

05:26.367 --> 05:29.579
♪ YOU'RE NO GOOD
FOR ME ♪

05:29.662 --> 05:32.415
♪ YOU'RE... ♪

05:32.498 --> 05:33.416
OK, YOU WIN.

05:33.499 --> 05:35.752
{\an1}BUT I'M DOING IT FOR
THE GUIDE, NOT LOOMER.

05:35.835 --> 05:37.837
JUST STOP THE LOOK.
IT BURNS.

05:37.920 --> 05:39.589
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT BURNS.

05:39.672 --> 05:41.841
THESE SUPERHOT
CHEESE PUFFS.

05:41.924 --> 05:43.551
{\an1}THEY'RE SO HOT,
THEY HURT.

05:46.804 --> 05:48.181
TRY ONE.

05:48.264 --> 05:49.057
NO, THANKS. I HAVE
TO FIGURE OUT A WAY

05:49.140 --> 05:51.267
TO GET LOOMER OFF THE HOOK,

05:51.350 --> 05:52.935
AND I NEED TO BE
ALIVE TO DO IT.

05:53.019 --> 05:54.687
I'LL TRY ONE.

05:56.647 --> 05:58.983
TASTY.

06:02.737 --> 06:04.781
WAIT A MINUTE.

06:10.411 --> 06:13.581
{\an1}ALL RIGHT, WE ALL KNOW
THAT LOOMER WAS CAUGHT...

06:16.793 --> 06:18.002
WITH REGULAR CHEESE PUFFS.

06:18.086 --> 06:21.714
{\an4}BUT WHEN I TESTED
THE CHEEDLE FOUND AT
THE SCENE AT THE CRIME,

06:21.798 --> 06:25.426
{\an1}IT CAME BACK
SUPERHOT FLAVOR.

06:29.847 --> 06:34.644
{\an4}WHICH MEANS LOOMER
CANNOT BE THE SANDER
SMASHER.

06:36.687 --> 06:39.107
I'M FREE!

06:39.190 --> 06:40.983
THAT WAS SO FAST.

06:41.067 --> 06:43.069
{\an1}WHY CAN'T I DO THAT
ON MY LAPTOP?

06:43.152 --> 06:45.822
'CAUSE I'M RUNNING DUAL
2.3 MEGAHERTZ PROCESSORS

06:45.905 --> 06:48.574
{\an1}WITH ONE TERABYTE
OF HARD DRIVE.

06:48.658 --> 06:50.243
AND YOU'RE RUNNING POOP.

06:50.326 --> 06:54.330
OH, I HATE THIS COMPUTER.
IT'S SO STUPID.

06:54.413 --> 06:56.249
IT'S SNORGLE NORGLE...

06:56.332 --> 06:58.835
[GARBLED CURSING]

06:58.918 --> 07:00.837
DAGGA SAGGA NAGGA...

07:00.920 --> 07:03.047
{\an1}[FEEDBACK]

07:05.299 --> 07:06.801
CARRY ON.

07:06.884 --> 07:11.305
{\an1}WELL, IF LOOMER DIDN'T
DO IT, THEN WHO DID?

07:11.389 --> 07:13.349
I'VE CROSS REFERENCED ALL
THE KIDS WITH HALL PASSES

07:13.432 --> 07:15.017
AT THE TIME OF THE CRIME

07:15.101 --> 07:17.603
{\an1}WITH ANYONE WHO WILL BE
FRUSTRATED WITH A BAD SANDER,

07:17.687 --> 07:21.691
{\an4}HAS A DETENTION RECORD,
AND ENJOYS SUPERHOT
CHEESE PUFFS.

07:21.774 --> 07:23.860
NICE.

07:23.943 --> 07:25.486
AND WITH THOSE STATS
COMBINED,

07:25.570 --> 07:28.906
{\an1}WE'LL COME UP WITH
A NUMBER ONE SUSPECT.

07:35.079 --> 07:35.705
THANKS.

07:35.788 --> 07:38.374
MR. CRUBBS,
MOZE IS INNOCENT.

07:38.457 --> 07:39.292
WE'LL SEE.

07:39.375 --> 07:40.251
BUT IF ANY MORE STUFF
GETS SMASHED,

07:40.334 --> 07:44.088
YOU TWO WILL BE JOINING
HER ON THAT BENCH.

07:44.172 --> 07:45.131
I'LL PUT EVERY KID
IN SCHOOL ON THAT BENCH

07:45.214 --> 07:49.010
UNTIL I FIND
THE CULPRIT.

07:57.977 --> 07:58.728
AAAAH!

07:58.811 --> 08:01.397
[SIREN]

08:03.191 --> 08:05.902
SOMEONE SMASHED
MY BASKETBALLS.

08:05.985 --> 08:08.654
{\an5}HOW ARE MY KIDS
GONNA SHOOT HOOPS
WITH SMASHED BALLS?

08:08.738 --> 08:11.657
{\an1}CALM DOWN. I'LL GET YOU
NEW ONES BY TOMORROW.

08:11.741 --> 08:13.117
BUT FIRST...

08:30.635 --> 08:32.260
[TOGETHER]
THIS STINKS.

08:32.345 --> 08:33.929
WHO WOULD DESTROY
SCHOOL PROPERTY

08:34.013 --> 08:35.014
AND UPSET THE TEACHERS?

08:35.097 --> 08:36.265
[LAUGHING]

08:36.349 --> 08:38.517
{\an1}THEY DON'T LOOK
THAT UPSET TO ME.

08:38.601 --> 08:40.602
{\an5}AREN'T YOU GUYS UPSET
THAT ALL YOUR STUFF
GOT SMASHED?

08:40.686 --> 08:42.605
{\an1}WELL, AT FIRST WE WERE,
BUT THEN CRUBBS SAID

08:42.688 --> 08:43.940
HE'D GET US NEW STUFF.

08:44.023 --> 08:46.943
{\an5}I AM SO NOT SORRY
TO SEE THOSE OLD
BASKETBALLS GONE.

08:47.026 --> 08:49.070
THEY BARELY BOUNCED
ANYMORE.

08:49.153 --> 08:50.947
{\an1}I WISH SOMEBODY WOULD SMASH
THAT VCR IN MY ROOM.

08:51.030 --> 08:53.574
I CAN'T REWIND.

08:53.658 --> 08:55.326
MAYBE THIS ISN'T A BAD KID
DOING BAD THINGS.

08:55.409 --> 08:57.828
{\an1}MAYBE IT'S JUST A GOOD
KID DOING BAD THINGS

08:57.912 --> 08:59.247
FOR A GOOD REASON.

08:59.330 --> 09:02.166
{\an1}MAYBE THIS SMASHER MASHER
VANDALIZES FOR GOOD, NOT EVIL.

09:02.250 --> 09:03.709
WORK YOUR COMPUTER AGAIN,

09:03.793 --> 09:05.378
{\an1}BUT THIS TIME, TAKE OUT
THE DETENTION RECORD

09:05.461 --> 09:07.880
AND GIVE ME
A NEW LIST OF SUSPECTS.

09:18.182 --> 09:20.476
Moze: WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

09:20.559 --> 09:21.811
WE SET A TRAP.

09:21.894 --> 09:23.729
WE NEED BATE.
SOMEONE SWEET

09:23.813 --> 09:25.106
{\an1}WHO CAN PULL OFF SYMPATHY
AND LEAD THE SMASHER

09:25.189 --> 09:27.066
RIGHT INTO JUSTICE.

09:27.149 --> 09:28.150
BUT WHO?

09:31.070 --> 09:33.155
OK, I'LL DO IT.

09:33.239 --> 09:34.448
YES!

09:35.449 --> 09:39.287
{\an1}WAIT. WE CAN'T
JUST LEAVE THE BENCH.

09:46.377 --> 09:49.213
OH, THIS VCR IS THE WORST!

09:49.297 --> 09:52.675
HOW I WISH I HAD A NEW ONE!

09:52.758 --> 09:56.137
IF ANYBODY NEEDS ME, I WILL BE
IN THE TEACHER'S LOUNGE

09:56.220 --> 10:00.266
AWAY FROM THIS RETCHED VCR,

10:00.349 --> 10:03.686
WHICH WILL BE IN MY ROOM
THAT IS UNLOCKED

10:03.769 --> 10:05.479
WITH ME NOT IN IT.

10:16.449 --> 10:17.992
OW!

10:19.201 --> 10:20.786
NOW WE WAIT.

10:28.002 --> 10:28.961
AHA!

10:28.002 --> 10:28.961
{\an1}AHA!

10:29.045 --> 10:31.047
BUSTED!

10:31.130 --> 10:34.216
NO. NO. I JUST LEFT
MY NOTEBOOK HERE.

10:35.676 --> 10:35.926
{\an1}COME ON.

10:36.010 --> 10:38.763
OW! OW!

10:43.017 --> 10:44.935
AHA!

10:45.019 --> 10:46.103
{\an1}BUSTED!

10:46.187 --> 10:47.229
OH. NO. I'M LEAVING
MY CARD

10:47.313 --> 10:48.272
FOR MR. MONROE
IN CASE HE WANTS TO

10:48.356 --> 10:50.232
SUE THE
A.V. DEPARTMENT.

10:50.316 --> 10:52.777
COME ON! GET IN!

10:59.075 --> 11:00.451
BUSTED!

11:00.534 --> 11:01.410
{\an5}NO, I WAS JUST
LEAVING A NOTE
TO TELL MR. MONROE

11:01.494 --> 11:02.912
TO TRY A VCR FUNDRAISER
TO RAISE MONEY--

11:02.995 --> 11:05.748
{\an1}COME ON!

11:16.842 --> 11:17.927
{\an3}[SMASH]

11:18.010 --> 11:19.303
AHA!

11:19.387 --> 11:25.226
THIS DOESN'T LOOK
GOOD, DOES IT?

11:25.309 --> 11:27.103
VICE PRINCIPALS AT TIMES
CAN SEEM TOUGHER

11:27.186 --> 11:28.187
THAN THE TOUGHEST BULLY,

11:28.270 --> 11:32.149
BUT JUST REMEMBER
THEY ALL FOLLOW THE SAME CODE:

11:32.233 --> 11:34.777
HONESTY IS ALWAYS
THE BEST POLICY.

11:34.860 --> 11:37.446
{\an5}MY CLIENT FOUND
THE SLEDGEHAMMER
AND THOUGHT

11:37.530 --> 11:40.241
{\an5}THAT MR. MONROE'S
CLASS WAS ACTUALLY
THE WOODSHOP

11:40.324 --> 11:41.909
AND WAS SIMPLY
RETURNING IT,

11:41.992 --> 11:45.496
LIKE THE UPSTANDING
STUDENT SHE IS.

11:45.579 --> 11:47.540
IS THAT THE TRUTH, LISA?

11:47.623 --> 11:51.794
{\an1}NO. AS CLASS TREASURER,
I DISCOVERED SCHOOL POLICY

11:51.877 --> 11:54.630
{\an1}MAKES IT IMPOSSIBLE
TO GET SUPPLIES REPLACED

11:54.713 --> 11:57.925
UNLESS THEY'RE INOPERABLE
OR STOLEN.

11:58.008 --> 12:01.095
I JUST WANTED TO HELP.

12:01.178 --> 12:04.974
{\an4}I APPRECIATE YOUR HONESTY,
AND SINCE YOU HAVE A CLEAN
RECORD,

12:05.057 --> 12:12.523
{\an4}I'M GONNA LET YOU OFF
WITH A WARNING, BUT
NO MORE VANDALISM.

12:12.606 --> 12:16.235
{\an1}NO SMASHING, NO CRASHING,
AND NO MASHING.

12:16.318 --> 12:18.946
[SMASHING]

12:19.029 --> 12:22.283
I REALLY NEEDED
A NEW COMPUTER.

12:22.366 --> 12:24.160
BUT LET'S ALL KEEP
THIS A SECRET, OK?

12:24.243 --> 12:27.163
WE DON'T WANT ALL THE TEACHERS
KNOWING THEY CAN GET NEW STUFF

12:27.246 --> 12:29.373
BY SMASHING THE OLD STUFF.

12:31.250 --> 12:33.210
MY HAND IS ON
THE P.A. BUTTON, ISN'T IT?

12:35.171 --> 12:37.298
[FEEDBACK]

12:37.381 --> 12:39.717
{\an1}[SMASH]

12:39.800 --> 12:41.218
[CRASH]

12:46.557 --> 12:49.268
{\an1}Ned: MONDAY: THE END
OF A FUN WEEKEND

12:49.351 --> 12:51.687
AND THE START OF A LONG
SCHOOL WEEK.

12:51.770 --> 12:53.814
AND IT AFFECTS EVERYBODY
DIFFERENTLY.

12:55.774 --> 12:59.195
YOU'VE GOT YOUR TIRED...

12:59.278 --> 13:00.196
AND YOUR TOTALLY CRANKY...

13:00.279 --> 13:01.155
MORNING.

13:01.238 --> 13:04.533
[GROWL]

13:04.617 --> 13:07.369
BUT SOMEHOW SOME PEOPLE ARE
TOTALLY IMMUNE TO MONDAYS.

13:07.453 --> 13:08.078
MOZE.

13:08.162 --> 13:09.872
HOPE YOU HAD
A GREAT WEEKEND.

13:09.955 --> 13:12.708
{\an1}AND HERE'S TO
A GREATER MONDAY.

13:14.126 --> 13:17.379
{\an1}Ned: AND SOME
ARE HIGHLY ALLERGIC.

13:17.463 --> 13:19.256
EHHH.

13:31.477 --> 13:32.394
{\an1}[SNORING]

13:32.478 --> 13:33.604
I HATE MONDAYS.

13:33.687 --> 13:36.232
{\an5}I'M TIRED,
I'M CRANKY,
AND HONESTLY,

13:36.315 --> 13:38.234
{\an5}MY BRAIN DOESN'T
START WORKING
UNTIL TUESDAY.

13:40.861 --> 13:41.946
OW.

13:42.029 --> 13:43.906
{\an5}WE'VE GOT TO
FIND A WAY TO
SURVIVE MONDAYS.

13:43.989 --> 13:45.908
I WEAR MY FAVORITE PAIR
OF UNDERWEAR TO SCHOOL

13:45.991 --> 13:47.076
EVERY MONDAY.

13:47.159 --> 13:48.869
{\an1}THE ELASTIC IS
PERFECTLY STRETCHED,

13:48.953 --> 13:50.287
THE COTTON IS
SLIGHTLY WORN,

13:50.371 --> 13:51.455
AND THE FLAP'S ALL-

13:51.539 --> 13:52.915
UH!

13:52.998 --> 13:55.459
WE NEED A PLAN
BETTER THAN UNDIES.

13:55.543 --> 13:59.129
{\an5}WE NEED A GREAT BIG
PLAN TO MAKE MONDAYS
FUN DAYS.

14:01.340 --> 14:02.675
OW!

14:02.758 --> 14:04.260
I'M IN AS LONG AS YOU PROMISE

14:04.343 --> 14:06.512
{\an1}NEVER TO SAY THE WORD
"FUN DAYS" AGAIN.

14:06.595 --> 14:08.222
[BELL RINGS]

14:06.595 --> 14:08.222
{\an3}WAKE UP!

14:08.305 --> 14:10.391
{\an1}WE'RE GONNA NEED
A BIGGER BOAT.

14:10.474 --> 14:14.270
{\an5}IF I CATCH YOU
IN ANOTHER ONE OF YOUR
ALL-DAY MONDAY NAPS,

14:14.353 --> 14:15.312
I'LL SEND YOU HOME...

14:15.396 --> 14:16.522
FOR GOOD!

14:16.605 --> 14:17.022
{\an1}[SNORE]

14:17.106 --> 14:19.108
{\an1}[THUD]

14:21.652 --> 14:22.903
GORDY'S NOT SLEEPING.

14:22.987 --> 14:23.654
HE'S JUST, UH,
GOING THROUGH

14:23.737 --> 14:25.781
{\an1}ANOTHER ONE OF HIS
FAINT SPELLS.

14:25.864 --> 14:28.450
RIGHT. HE'S
IRON DEFICIENT.

14:28.534 --> 14:29.910
GORDY, CAN YOU FEEL THIS?

14:29.994 --> 14:32.955
HOW I LOVE YOU,
HOW I LOVE YOU...

14:33.038 --> 14:34.415
THIS IS YOUR
LAST WARNING

14:34.498 --> 14:36.000
OR YOU'RE FIRED.

14:39.545 --> 14:40.045
[THUD]

14:43.507 --> 14:44.925
YOU CAN'T GET FIRED.

14:45.009 --> 14:45.801
{\an1}WHO'S GONNA GIVE US
MANLY ADVICE

14:45.884 --> 14:48.512
{\an1}OR GIVE US ENCOURAGEMENT
TO DO OUR BEST?

14:48.596 --> 14:50.931
OR LOAN US YOUR
MASTER KEYS?

14:51.015 --> 14:51.098
HERE, THANKS.

14:53.809 --> 14:57.229
{\an1}I CAN'T HELP IT. THERE'S
THIS NOISY BLUEBIRD

14:57.313 --> 14:58.355
{\an1}THAT KEEPS ME AWAKE
ON SUNDAY NIGHTS

14:58.439 --> 15:01.275
{\an1}WHEN I'M TRYING TO RECOVER
FROM MY WEEKEND ANTICS,

15:01.358 --> 15:03.986
{\an1}WHICH I'LL TELL YOU
MORE ABOUT WHEN YOU'RE 30.

15:04.069 --> 15:08.824
{\an4}I BETTER TAKE THIS,
1, BECAUSE I'M
A TECHNICAL WHIZ

15:08.907 --> 15:11.744
{\an1}AND 2, YOU GUYS
ARE USELESS ON MONDAYS.

15:11.827 --> 15:12.911
{\an1}HEY!

15:11.827 --> 15:12.911
HEY!

15:12.995 --> 15:14.246
AH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

15:12.995 --> 15:14.246
AH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

15:14.330 --> 15:15.456
[THUD]

15:15.539 --> 15:16.540
INTERESTING.

15:16.624 --> 15:19.460
{\an1}OK, COOKIE, YOU WORK ON
FIXING GORDY'S MONDAY SNOOZE

15:19.543 --> 15:22.129
{\an1}WHILE WE WORK ON BEATING
THE MONDAY BLUES.

15:23.464 --> 15:25.257
[LAUGHTER]

15:26.050 --> 15:28.969
{\an1}I MEAN, WHO DOESN'T
LOVE MONKEYS?

15:29.720 --> 15:32.640
I THINK I HAVE THE CURE.

15:35.809 --> 15:37.686
MONKEY MONDAYS?

15:37.770 --> 15:39.980
MONKEYS MAKE
EVERYTHING BETTER.

15:40.064 --> 15:41.523
WHY NOT MONDAYS?

15:41.607 --> 15:43.901
{\an5}MR. MONROE
BORROWED IT FROM
HIS ZOO FRIEND LADY.

15:43.984 --> 15:44.693
THAT'S RIGHT.
NED THOUGHT BOBO

15:44.777 --> 15:47.279
WOULD BRIGHTEN UP
YOUR MONDAY.

15:47.363 --> 15:48.197
WON'T THAT BE FUN?

15:48.280 --> 15:50.699
{\an1}NOW, BE CAREFUL
AND DON'T SCARE IT.

15:50.783 --> 15:53.202
{\an1}YOU KNOW, IT'S MONDAY,
AND I HAVE TO ADMIT,

15:53.285 --> 15:55.079
I DO FEEL BETTER.

15:55.162 --> 15:55.371
[SCREECHING]

15:55.454 --> 15:57.539
AAAH!

15:57.623 --> 15:58.499
AAAH!

15:58.582 --> 16:02.586
[BOTH SCREAMING]

16:07.299 --> 16:10.052
OK, SO MONKEY MONDAYS
WASN'T THE ANSWER,

16:10.135 --> 16:11.804
BUT WE CANNOT
LET MONDAYS BEAT US.

16:11.887 --> 16:13.555
WE CANNOT GIVE UP.

16:13.639 --> 16:15.474
{\an1}I THINK IT POOPED
ON YOUR HEAD.

16:15.557 --> 16:17.810
[KIDS SCREAMING]

16:20.813 --> 16:22.731
SHH! HE'S ASLEEP.

16:22.815 --> 16:24.316
THAT'S NOT A GOOD
THING, REMEMBER?

16:24.400 --> 16:27.403
IT'S VERY GOOD
BECAUSE IT'S MY NEW

16:27.486 --> 16:30.030
CRAM MASTER WAKE MASTER.

16:30.114 --> 16:31.657
GORDY LOOKS AWAKE AND
WORKING WHENEVER CRUBBS

16:31.740 --> 16:34.618
COMES WITHIN 40 FEET.

16:39.623 --> 16:42.084
THAT'S BETTER.

16:42.167 --> 16:43.001
IT WORKED.

16:43.085 --> 16:45.671
OK, BUT BE CAREFUL
WITH THE CRAM MASTER.

16:45.754 --> 16:46.964
THAT THING
BRAINWASHED ME.

16:47.047 --> 16:48.799
NOW WHENEVER I CAN'T
FIGURE SOMETHING OUT,

16:48.882 --> 16:51.385
{\an5}ABE LINCOLN AND
BENEDICT ARNOLD APPEAR
ON MY SHOULDERS.

16:51.468 --> 16:53.679
NOW, NED, LET ME
JUST SAY.

16:53.762 --> 16:55.347
WOO HOO HOO!

16:55.431 --> 16:57.766
GO AWAY, PLEASE.

17:07.859 --> 17:10.362
I BETTER GO MAKE
SOME ADJUSTMENTS.

17:10.445 --> 17:12.321
{\an1}Mr. Monroe:
NO! BOBO! NO!

17:14.867 --> 17:17.453
SO WHAT'S OUR
NEXT MONDAY MOVE?

17:17.536 --> 17:18.954
I DON'T KNOW.

17:19.038 --> 17:21.165
{\an4}WE NEED SOMETHING
TO BREAK THROUGH THAT
MONDAY MIND CLOG,

17:21.248 --> 17:22.374
{\an1}BUT WHAT?

17:24.710 --> 17:26.837
{\an1}MEGAPHONE MONDAYS:
THE EXTRA LOUD CONVERSATIONS

17:26.920 --> 17:28.797
{\an1}WILL BREAK THROUGH
THE MONDAY BRAIN BLOCK,

17:28.881 --> 17:31.592
{\an1}AND I GAVE THEM TO ALL
OUR FRIENDS.

17:31.675 --> 17:34.803
HI, GUYS! HAPPY MONDAY!

17:37.723 --> 17:39.099
MAYBE THEY'RE
A LITTLE LOUD.

17:39.183 --> 17:41.685
[BEEPING]

17:41.769 --> 17:45.314
THE WAKE MASTER CRASHED.
AND SO DID GORDY.

17:45.397 --> 17:47.941
AND HERE COMES
MR. CRUBBS.

17:49.443 --> 17:50.736
[SIREN]

17:50.819 --> 17:51.820
MORNING SAUSAGE!

17:51.904 --> 17:53.155
MY BIG, MY BIG.

17:53.238 --> 17:54.364
AHEM.

17:54.448 --> 17:57.576
THAT IS A CLEAN FLOOR HERE,
COOKIE, A VERY CLEAN FLOOR.

17:59.661 --> 18:02.247
{\an1}WE GOT TO FIND ANOTHER WAY
TO KEEP GORDY AWAKE.

18:02.331 --> 18:03.540
I WILL NOT GIVE UP AND
I WILL FIND ANOTHER WAY

18:03.624 --> 18:06.126
TO BEAT MONDAYS.

18:07.961 --> 18:09.129
MACCHIATO MONDAYS.

18:09.213 --> 18:09.713
{\an5}MY MOM SAYS
THEY REALLY
GIVE HER A BOOST

18:09.797 --> 18:11.131
TO GET THROUGH
THE DAY.

18:14.593 --> 18:16.136
TOO MUCH BOOST.

18:16.220 --> 18:17.513
CAN'T STOP BLINKING.

18:17.596 --> 18:20.307
CAN'T STOP TRYING
TO BEAT MONDAYS.

18:25.395 --> 18:27.272
MATZO BALL MONDAYS?

18:27.356 --> 18:29.024
THAT'S IT?
THAT'S WHAT

18:29.107 --> 18:32.611
SCHOOL SURVIVAL GENIUS
NED BIGBY CAME UP WITH?

18:32.694 --> 18:34.363
IT'S THE ONLY "M" WORD
I COULD THINK OF, OK?

18:34.446 --> 18:35.739
I CAN'T THINK ON MONDAYS.

18:35.823 --> 18:37.616
WHERE ARE
THE MATZO BALLS?

18:39.618 --> 18:42.538
NO, BOBO, NO!

18:49.628 --> 18:50.963
OH, MONDAY.

18:51.046 --> 18:54.299
WHAT SURPRISE WILL
YOU BRING ME NEXT?

18:58.971 --> 19:01.723
{\an1}THAT'S IT! MONDAY WINS.
I GIVE UP.

19:01.807 --> 19:03.684
WHAT?
YOU'RE KIDDING.

19:03.767 --> 19:05.727
{\an1}YOU'VE NEVER GIVEN UP AT
ANYTHING IN YOUR LIFE.

19:05.811 --> 19:07.938
WELL, I'M GIVING UP NOW.
I'M DONE.

19:09.022 --> 19:11.358
OK, MONDAY, YOU WIN.

19:11.441 --> 19:12.818
YOU WIN!

19:12.901 --> 19:14.945
[KIDS SCREAMING]

19:17.447 --> 19:21.577
NED, I FINALLY FIGURED OUT
A WAY TO KEEP GORDY AWAKE.

19:21.660 --> 19:26.707
{\an1}SAY HELLO TO
THE WAKE MASTER...2.

19:26.790 --> 19:27.916
{\an1}WHENEVER GORDY'S PULSE
FALLS BELOW 50,

19:28.000 --> 19:32.004
{\an1}HE'LL RECEIVE A MILD
SHOCK AND WAKE UP.

19:32.087 --> 19:33.088
HOW MILD?

19:39.011 --> 19:40.846
AHA, SLEEPING AGAIN.

19:40.929 --> 19:42.598
THAT'S IT, GORDON,
YOU'RE FIRED.

19:42.681 --> 19:44.892
AND NOTHING WILL
CHANGE MY MIND.

19:44.975 --> 19:47.269
WHAT IF I CATCH
THE MONKEY?

19:47.352 --> 19:48.979
NO!

19:49.062 --> 19:52.065
OK, YES, BUT
DO IT TODAY.

19:55.402 --> 19:59.239
{\an5}OK, I'M GONNA NEED
A TOTALLY REDESIGNED
WAKE MASTER

19:59.323 --> 20:00.574
WITHOUT
THE ELECTRIC SHOCKS.

20:00.657 --> 20:03.201
{\an5}ONE, BECAUSE I
HAVE TO BE WIDE AWAKE
WHEN I CATCH THAT MONEY

20:03.285 --> 20:05.787
{\an5}AND ALSO I STILL
MIGHT WANT TO HAVE KIDS
SOMEDAY.

20:05.871 --> 20:10.375
I THINK I HAVE
JUST THE THING.

20:16.131 --> 20:19.760
CAN YOU BELIEVE IT'S
LINCOLN'S BIRTHDAY?

20:19.843 --> 20:22.596
JUST ANOTHER THING
TO LOVE ABOUT MONDAY.

20:25.766 --> 20:28.393
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH NED?

20:28.477 --> 20:32.105
{\an1}HE'S ALLERGIC TO MONDAYS LIKE
I'M ALLERGIC TO CATS, DOGS,

20:32.189 --> 20:34.942
{\an1}TRESS, NUTS, AND RAP VIDEOS
THAT EXPLOIT WOMEN.

20:35.025 --> 20:38.528
I'VE NEVER SEEN HIM
LIKE THIS.

20:38.612 --> 20:40.489
HE JUST KIND OF
GAVE UP.

20:40.572 --> 20:42.366
HE JUST COULDN'T MAKE
MONDAYS FUN DAYS.

20:44.242 --> 20:46.411
YOU KNOW,
IF I GAVE UP,

20:46.495 --> 20:48.372
I MIGHT NOT
HAVE BEEN ABLE

20:48.455 --> 20:50.791
TO KEEP OUR GREAT
COUNTRY TOGETHER.

20:50.874 --> 20:55.671
{\an5}BUT I DID NOT GIVE UP
AND NOW YOU CELEBRATE
MY BIRTHDAY EVERY--

20:55.754 --> 20:57.631
HEY, WHY
ARE YOU IN SCHOOL?

20:57.714 --> 20:59.841
{\an5}YOU'RE
SUPPOSED TO HAVE
MY BIRTHDAY OFF.

20:59.925 --> 21:01.343
WE DON'T ANYMORE.

21:01.426 --> 21:03.136
WE LUMPED YOU AND ALL THE
OTHER PRESIDENTS TOGETHER

21:03.220 --> 21:05.430
AND MADE PRESIDENTS' DAY.

21:05.514 --> 21:05.722
PRESIDENTS' DAY?

21:05.806 --> 21:07.766
HELLO?

21:07.849 --> 21:09.559
{\an1}YEAH, BUT YOU CAN GET GREAT
DEALS ON HOME ELECTRONICS

21:09.643 --> 21:10.686
ON YOUR BIRTHDAY.

21:10.769 --> 21:11.436
YEAH, RIGHT.

21:11.520 --> 21:14.564
I SAVED AMERICA
FROM SECESSION

21:14.648 --> 21:18.026
AND NOW I CAN SAVE YOU
MONEY ON DVD PLAYERS.

21:18.110 --> 21:20.320
{\an1}HA HA HA!

21:20.404 --> 21:21.947
OH, IT'S OK.

21:22.030 --> 21:23.281
{\an5}HE'S JUST TALKING
TO TINY IMAGINARY
HISTORICAL FIGURES.

21:23.365 --> 21:26.451
CAN YOU GUYS BE IMAGINARY
ON THE DESK?

21:26.535 --> 21:28.328
THIS HURTS MY NECK.

21:28.412 --> 21:32.499
{\an4}NED, YOU CANNOT
GIVE UP TRYING TO MAKE
MONDAYS FUN DAYS.

21:32.582 --> 21:35.210
{\an1}GIVING UP IS NEVER
THE ANSWER TO ANYTHING.

21:35.293 --> 21:37.379
{\an5}YEAH, YOU KNOW,
OLD FREAKY BEARD
HAS GOT A POINT.

21:37.462 --> 21:38.672
IF THE BRITISH
HADN'T GIVEN UP,

21:38.755 --> 21:40.799
I'D BE ON THE
FIVE DOLLAR BILL!

21:40.882 --> 21:44.052
{\an4}SOMETIMES, NED,
IF YOU LOOK CLOSE,
YOU WILL FIND

21:44.136 --> 21:45.971
{\an1}THE ANSWER IS OFTEN
RIGHT IN FRONT OF YOU.

21:46.054 --> 21:48.473
Lisa: ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

21:48.557 --> 21:50.434
DO YOU NEED HELP
WITH SOMETHING?

21:50.517 --> 21:53.729
{\an1}YES. HOW DO YOU GUYS
BEAT MONDAYS?

21:53.812 --> 21:57.065
OH, THAT'S EASY.

21:58.650 --> 22:00.027
Gordy: AH!

22:02.237 --> 22:03.864
IT'S AMAZING WHAT
YOU CAN DO ON MONDAYS

22:03.947 --> 22:06.408
WHEN YOU'RE WIDE AWAKE.

22:06.491 --> 22:08.201
{\an1}IF A BIRD COULD KEEP HIM
AWAKE ALL NIGHT,

22:08.285 --> 22:11.997
2 BIRDS COULD
KEEP HIM AWAKE ALL DAY.

22:15.667 --> 22:17.753
I THINK THEY
POOPED ON HIS HEAD.

22:20.172 --> 22:22.299
Ned: THERE'S 52 MONDAYS
A YEAR.

22:22.382 --> 22:24.926
{\an1}TAKE OUT SUMMER BREAK,
MONDAY HOLIDAYS,

22:25.010 --> 22:26.553
AND 2 MORE
FOR SPRING AND WINTER BREAK,

22:26.636 --> 22:28.805
THEN THERE'S ONLY 35 MONDAYS
TO SURVIVE,

22:28.889 --> 22:29.848
AND THESE TIPS WILL HELP.

22:29.931 --> 22:32.059
TAKE COOKIE'S COMFY UNDIES TIP
ONE STEP FARTHER

22:32.142 --> 22:34.644
{\an8}AND WEAR YOUR FAVORITE OUTFIT.

22:34.728 --> 22:36.480
{\an8}IT'LL MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER.

22:36.563 --> 22:38.148
MONDAY.

22:38.231 --> 22:41.109
{\an1}LISA ZEMO PACKS A FAVORITE
AND SPECIAL LUNCH ON MONDAYS,

22:41.193 --> 22:43.403
{\an7}SO MAKE MONDAY
FAVORITE LUNCH DAY.

22:43.487 --> 22:44.780
{\an1}IT'LL GIVE YOU SOMETHING
TO LOOK FORWARD TO

22:44.863 --> 22:49.451
ALL MORNING LONG.

22:49.534 --> 22:50.786
HAM!

22:49.534 --> 22:50.786
HAM!

22:53.747 --> 22:55.540
COCONUT HEAD GOES
TO THE MOVIES EVERY MONDAY,

22:55.624 --> 22:56.833
{\an1}SO PLAN SOMETHING SPECIAL
THAT YOU CAN LOOK FORWARD TO

22:56.917 --> 22:58.001
ALL SCHOOL DAY LONG

22:58.085 --> 23:00.962
AND MAKE MONDAYS FUN DAYS.

23:01.046 --> 23:03.590
HEY, EVERYBODY,
THANKS TO NED,

23:03.673 --> 23:06.510
YOU CAN ALL ENJOY
MOVIE MONDAY!

23:06.593 --> 23:08.887
[CHEERING]

23:14.893 --> 23:16.895
OH, A MONKEY
MOVIE.

23:16.978 --> 23:19.147
WHERE IS
MY POPPING CORN?

23:19.231 --> 23:21.817
GIVE ME BACK MY
POPPING CORN, SIR.

23:21.900 --> 23:24.319
OH, IS THIS YOURS?

23:24.402 --> 23:25.487
{\an3}YEAH.

23:25.570 --> 23:26.488
[BLOWS RASPBERRY]

23:26.571 --> 23:27.447
{\an1}HA HA!

23:27.531 --> 23:30.367
YOU ARE JUST
IMMATURE.

23:30.450 --> 23:32.452
{\an1}YEAH, IMMATURE
WITH POPCORN, RIGHT?

23:32.536 --> 23:36.039
